# KDF Rider app ‚Äî permanent EAS / API rules

## Project path

All Rider work and builds start from:

`artifacts/kdf-mobile`

Run EAS **only** from that directory (or pass the equivalent project path). A separate `eas.json` exists at the monorepo root for other tooling; Rider builds use `artifacts/kdf-mobile/eas.json` and `app.json` there.

### Expo dashboard label `@workspace/kdf-mobile`

That string is the **npm package name** from `artifacts/kdf-mobile/package.json`. It does **not** mean the whole monorepo is the ‚ÄúExpo project‚Äù; the linked `extra.eas.projectId` in `app.json` is the Expo project identity.

### Queue vs wrong upload

**Queued ‚Äî Free Tier Queue** means the job has not started on a builder yet (Expo capacity). It is normal for free tier to wait a long time; it does **not** by itself prove the archive was wrong. Smaller uploads still help (faster upload step and less to unpack).

### Smaller Git archives

- Repo root **`.easignore`** trims the **Git** archive (high impact: excludes `attached_assets/`, all `node_modules/`, caches, build outputs).
- **`artifacts/kdf-mobile/.easignore`** adds app-local junk only. **Do not** ignore `pnpm-lock.yaml` here ‚Äî that was incorrectly listed before and would drop the monorepo lockfile from the upload.

## Production API (non-negotiable)

- **Always** bake: `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.khanbabadryfruits.com`
- **Never** use `https://khanbabadryfruits.com` (or `www`) as the Rider **API** base ‚Äî that is the storefront/static host; Rider auth and `/api/*` must hit **Express api-server** only.
- `eas.json` must keep that env on **every** build profile that ships to real riders (`development` / `preview` / `production` / `play-store`).
- `context/AuthContext.tsx` already remaps storefront/admin hosts to `https://api.khanbabadryfruits.com`; do not remove that guard.

`app.json` `expo-router` **origin** may stay `https://khanbabadryfruits.com/` for deep links ‚Äî that is not the API URL.

## Standard production APK build (Expo cloud)

From `artifacts/kdf-mobile`:

```bash
npx eas-cli@latest build -p android --profile production --non-interactive
```

- **`production`** profile = **internal distribution + release APK** + production API URL (see `eas.json`).
- For **Google Play AAB**, use profile **`play-store`** (or `pnpm run build:play-store`).

## Before building

Confirm API is up:

```bash
curl -sS "https://api.khanbabadryfruits.com/api/healthz"
```

Expected body includes: `"status":"ok"` and `"service":"@workspace/api-server"`.

## Expo auth (local / CI)

- Set `EXPO_TOKEN` in the environment when running non-interactive builds (EAS account token).
- Builds upload to Expo; download the APK from the Expo build page (or EAS CLI artifacts).

## Goal workflow after code changes

1. Update code under `artifacts/kdf-mobile`
2. Run the EAS command above (or `pnpm run build:apk`)
3. Download APK from Expo
4. Install on devices
